-- Turkey Bad Checks at 2-Year High After Jail Scrapped, Vatan Says
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-06-18T06:56:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-18/turkey-bad-checks-at-2-year-high-after-jail-scrapped-vatan-says.html
Turkey  reported the highest number
of bounced checks in two years in May after the government
scrapped jail terms for those convicted of passing the checks,
 Vatan newspaper  reported.  Istanbul Chamber of Commerce President Murat Yalcintas
called for immediate steps to counter the increase, including
the introduction of financial risk insurance products, the
Istanbul-based newspaper said. Turkey recorded 83,080 bad checks
in May, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
